          <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="during-development">During development</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">If you write or manage custom code, you must check it for security vulnerabilities. This helps you:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>find and fix vulnerabilities</li>
            <li>improve the quality of your software</li>
            <li>meet coding standards</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="govuk-body">Use automated tools to pick up errors and vulnerable libraries that you have used. Examples of automated tools include Nessus, Rapid7 and Qualys.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">After doing automated tests, ask a security expert to check for vulnerabilities that are harder to find. If you do not have a security expert on your team, you can <a href=mailto:UKStratComDD-IES-SI-CRP-VR@mod.gov.uk target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>ask for help with manual testing</a>.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Find out <a href="" target="_blank">which automated tools are used in Defence<span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span></a>.</p>  
        <p class="govuk-body">Check <a href="https://gds-way.digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk/manuals/code-review-guidelines.html#content" target="_blank">GOV.UK guidance on code reviews<span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span></a>.</p>


